Governor Yahaya Bello of Kogi State has described the passing of former Anambra State gov­ernor, Dr. Chinwoke Mbadinu­ju as a great loss to the nation, while expressing condolences to the Government and People of Anambra State, family and friends of the deceased. A condolence message signed by Onogwu Mu­hammed, Chief Press Sec­retary to the Governor, and made available to newsmen in Lokoja on Wednesday, Bello said he was humbled and sad­dened by Mbadinuju’s death. “I am humbled and sad­dened by the news of the death of former Governor of Anambra State, His Excel­lency Chinwoke Mbadinuju. His death is a great loss to us all, and his contributions to Anambra State in particular where he served as governor between 1999 and 2003 and Nigeria in general will always remain prominent.” Bello offers his sincere condolences to the people of Anambra State, family, friends and associates of the deceased and prays that the Almighty God grants them the strength and comfort to weather the difficult period. “To the family, friends and associates of His Excellen­cy, Chinwoke Mbadinuju , I share in your grief, and I offer my sincere condolences to you. May the Almighty God grant you the strength and comfort to weather this difficult peri­od,” the statement said. Bello said that the former governor who was also for­mer editor of Times Interna­tional and associate professor of politics and African studies at the State University of New York was a visionary leader who had a clear understand­ing of the challenges facing his state and painstakingly designed programmes and policies that prioritised the security of his people while providing a level playing field for all.